\p
\v 12 Just like a \add human\add* body is a unit butÂŠ118056 has many parts which are all components, no matter how many, making up that one body, so too is the \nd messiahÂŠ118079\nd*.\x + \xo 12:12: \xt Rom 12:4-5.\x*
\v 13 \add Yes,\add* in one spirit we were all immersedÂŠ118090 into one bodyÂŠ118089, whether \add we were\add* Jews or GreeksÂŠ118094, whether slavesÂŠ118096 or free, and we all were given one spirit to drinkÂŠ118105. MEANING?
\p
\v 14 \add Yes,\add* indeed the bodyÂŠ118110 is not one part, butÂŠ118115 many.
\v 15 If \add your\add* foot said, âSince I'm not a hand, I'm not part of the body,â that wouldn't make it any less a part of the body,
