\v 21 \add YourÂŠ118223\add* eyeÂŠ118217 can't tell \add your\add* handÂŠ118221, âI don't need you,â and \add your\add* headÂŠ118229 can't tell \add your\add* feetÂŠ118231, âI don't need you.â
\v 22 On the contrary, the bodyÂŠ118243 partsÂŠ118241 that seem to be weakerÂŠ118244 are \add very\add* vital,
\v 23 and those body parts thatÂŠ118249 seem less honourable, we give them greater honour and hence ourÂŠ118262 unpresentable body parts are \add treated with\add* more modesty.
\v 24 OurÂŠ118269 presentable parts don't have any need for that, butÂŠ118273 rather \nd GodÂŠ118276\nd* has put the bodyÂŠ118279 togetherÂŠ118277 and he gaveÂŠ118286 greater honourÂŠ118287 to the lesser parts
\v 25 so that thereÂŠ118290 won'tÂŠ118289 be any divisionÂŠ118292 in the bodyÂŠ118295, butÂŠ118296 its membersÂŠ118303 should care equally for each other.
\v 26 SoÂŠ118304 if one body part is hurting, all the parts hurt as well. If one body part is honoured, thenÂŠ118304 all the parts are happy together.
\p
