\v 3 Even if I gave everything I have \add to the poor\add*, andÂŠ118460 even sacrifice myÂŠ118458 bodyÂŠ118465 so that I could boastÂŠ118468, butÂŠ118472 didn'tÂŠ118473 loveÂŠ118471 \add others\add*, it wouldn't be any use to me.
\p
\v 4 Love is patientÂŠ118479 and kind. It doesn't envy \add others\add*, it doesn't boast, and it isn'tÂŠ118483 arrogantÂŠ118492.
\v 5 It isn'tÂŠ118493 crude, it doesn't just care about itselfÂŠ118501, it doesn't get angry quickly, and it doesn't keep records about who wrongs \add us\add*.
\v 6 Love isn'tÂŠ118508 happy with disobeying \add God\add*, butÂŠ118514 is happy about the truthÂŠ118516.
\v 7 It tolerates everything, believesÂŠ118522 everything, is always hopeful about everything, and always perseveres.
\p
\v 8 Love neverÂŠ118529 fails, unlike propheciesÂŠ118534 that will come to nothing, languagesÂŠ118539 that will die out, and knowledgeÂŠ118542 that \add also\add* will come to nothing,
\v 9 because we only have partial knowledge and partial \add understanding\add* of prophecyÂŠ118553.
