\v 11 When I was a child, I spoke like a child, thought like a child, and reasoned like a child, \add but\add* then when I became an adult, I set childish things aside.
\v 12 \add In this present age\add*, we see like fuzzy reflections in a mirrorÂŠ118591, but \add in the future\add*, we'll see \add God\add* face to face. In this age, I have partial knowledge, but then it'll be complete, just like \em we'll be knownÂŠ118609\em* completely.
\p
\v 13 ButÂŠ118623 for now, these threeÂŠ118617 continue: faithÂŠ118613, hope, and love, butÂŠ118611 love is the greatestÂŠ118622 one of those.
